icious. &nbsp;</p>         </div>              </div><div class=\"row\">                       <div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6  col-sm-6  col-xs-12\">             <a href=\"https://czickontheroad-962d.kxcdn.com/userfiles/images/post/medium/16 (1).jpg\" class=\"swipebox\" data-footer=\"Lomo saltado, another Peruvian food with Asian fusion. Beef tenderloin sauteed with Asian sauce and pisco, served with rice and fries. In some hip places, we also found a version with mushroom instead of beef – really delicious (recipe at the end of this article).\" title=\"Lomo saltado, another Peruvian food with Asian fusion. Beef tenderloin sauteed with Asian sauce and pisco, served with rice and fries. In some hip places, we also found a version with mushroom instead of beef – really delicious (recipe at the end of this article).\" data-toggle=\"lightbox\" data-gallery=\"gallery\">                 <img src=\"https://czickontheroad-962d.kxcdn.com/userfiles/images/post/medium/16 (1).jpg\" alt=\"Lomo saltado, another Peruvian food with Asian fusion. Beef tenderloin sauteed with Asian sauce and pisco, served with rice and fries. In some hip places, we also found a version with mushroom instead of beef – really delicious (recipe at the end of this article).\">             </a>             <p>Lomo saltado, another Peruvian food with Asian fusion. Beef tenderloin sauteed with Asian sauce and pisco, served with rice and fries. In some hip places, we also found a version with mushroom instead of beef – really delicious (recipe at the end of this article). &nbsp;</p>         </div>                       <div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6  col-sm-6  col-xs-12\">             <a href=\"https://czickontheroad-962d.kxcdn.com/userfiles/images/post/medium/28.jpg\" class=\"swipebox\" data-footer=\"Tallarin Saltado – same as Lomo Saltado, just that beef is mixed with noodles. It\'s very good, love the Asian sauce and crunchy onion and peppers.\" title=\"Tallarin Saltado – same as Lomo Saltado, just that beef is mixed with noodles. It\'s very good, love the Asian sauce and crunchy onion and peppers.\" data-toggle=\"lightbox\" data-gallery=\"gallery\">                 <img src=\"https://czickontheroad-962d.kxcdn.com/userfiles/images/post/medium/28.jpg\" alt=\"Tallarin Saltado – same as Lomo Saltado, just that beef is mixed with noodles. It\'s very good, love the Asian sauce and crunchy onion and peppers.\">             </a>             <p>Tallarin Saltado – same as Lomo Saltado, just that beef is mixed with noodles. It\'s very good, love the Asian sauce and crunchy onion and peppers. &nbsp;</p>         </div>              </div><div class=\"row\">                       <div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6  col-sm-6  col-xs-12\">             <a href=\"https://czickontheroad-962d.kxcdn.com/userfiles/images/post/medium/29.jpg\" class=\"swipebox\" data-footer=\"Tarmi con Asado – beef stew with rice and the white thing is some sort of mountain flower, which is actually poisonous until you soak it in water for several days...\" title=\"Tarmi con Asado – beef stew with rice and the white thing is some sort of mountain flower, which is actually poisonous until you soak it in water for several days...\" data-toggle=\"lightbox\" data-gallery=\"gallery\">                 <img src=\"https://czickontheroad-962d.kxcdn.com/userfiles/images/post/medium/29.jpg\" alt=\"Tarmi con Asado – beef stew with rice and the white thing is some sort of mountain flower, which is actually poisonous until you soak it in water for several days...\">             </a>             <p>Tarmi con Asado – beef stew with rice and the white thing is some sort of mountain flower, which is actually poisonous until you soak it in water for several days... &nbsp;</p>         </div>                       <div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6  col-sm-6  col-xs-12\">             <a href=\"https://czickontheroad-962d.kxcdn.com/userfiles/images/post/medium/30.jpg\" class=\"swipebox\" data-footer=\"Chicharon de Pollo – basically similar as KFC – deep fried pieces of chicken meat, very good. The more common version is chicharron de chancho – fried pork rinds.\" title=\"Chicharon de Pollo – basically similar as KFC – deep fried pieces of chicken meat, very good. The more common version is chicharron de chancho – fried pork rinds.\" data-toggle=\"lightbox\" data-gallery=\"gallery\">                 <img src=\"https://czickontheroad-962d.kxcdn.com/userfiles/images/post/medium/30.jpg\" alt=\"Chicharon de Pollo – basically similar as KFC – deep fried pieces of chicken meat, very good. The more common version is chicharron de chancho – fried pork rinds.\">             </a>             <p>Chicharon de Pollo – basically similar as KFC – deep fried pieces of chicken meat, very good. The more common version is chicharron de chancho – fried pork rinds. &nbsp;</p>         </div>              </div><div class=\"row\">                   </div> </div>\r\n\r\n<p>This is just a shortlist of all the delicous food Peru has to offer. I am a big lover of fish and sea foood, so had a great time on the coast, while Primoz more enjoyed the Ande\'s meat specialities. With more and more tourist coming, there are also many places offering just vegetarian dishes in bigger cities, just be ready to pay more for them...</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Recipe for Lomo Saltado / Sauteed Beef Tenderloin</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Prep. Time: 30 minutes&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Level: Easy</li>\r\n	<li>Servings: 4</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6  col-sm-6  col-xs-12\">\r\n<p>Ingredients:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 pound beef tenderloin – can be switched with champions for a veggie version</li>\r\n	<li>2 red onions, peeled and sliced into thick strips</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp; tomatoes sliced into thick strips</li>\r\n	<li>1 or 2 yellow chili pepper (Peruvian Aji Amarillo) cut in thin stripes</li>\r\n	<li>vegetable oil to fry as needed</li>\r\n	<li>Garlic chopped</li>\r\n	<li>Soy sauce, vinegar, beef/vegetable broth.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>3 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley</li>\r\n	<li>Salt, pepper, cumin, dried&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>French Fries 1 package (1 lb )</li>\r\n	<li>Pisco or brandy (1/2 cup)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Instructions:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a bowl marinate the meat with salt, pepper, and little cumin. Add the soy sauce. Set aside for 5 minutes. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a frying pan (medium-high heat). Add meat and fry until juices begin to release. Add a spoonful of garlic. Cook for 1 minute. Continuously move the pan and make fire (Sautee technique). Add a portion of onions until they are halfway transparent. Stir in the tomatoes and the yellow pepper. Cook until the tomatoes soften. Pour in a spoonful of soy sauce and ½ ounce of brandy. &nbsp;Cover and cook until beef is done. If preparation is too dry add 1 spoonful of vinegar or 2 spoons of beef broth. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and cumin. Sprinkle with chopped parsley to serve. Serve with white rice and potato fries. (you can also mix fries with the meat while finishing cooking, they will get soft and absorb the juice)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6  col-sm-6  col-xs-12\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/userfiles/images/lomo-saltado-recipe1.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>Do you like this Peruvian recipe? Pin it to your Cooking inspiration board &gt;&gt;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/userfiles/images/pinterest-peru-food.jpg\" style=\"width: 535px; height: 800px;\"></p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                                                                                                <div class=\"post-share\">\r\